    "# Perform PCA to reduce dimensions to 2D\n",

    "principal_components = pca.fit_transform(normalized_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Perform KMeans clustering with a specific number of clusters (k)\n",
    "k = 2\n",
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=0)\n",
    "kmeans.fit(principal_components)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assign clusters to each data point\n",
    "clusters = kmeans.predict(principal_components)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot clusters along with centroids\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot data points\n",
    "plt.scatter(principal_components[:, 0], principal_components[:, 1], c=clusters, cmap='viridis', s=50, alpha=0.5, label='Data Points')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot centroids\n",

    "def plot_knee_point(X, k):\n",
    "    nbrs = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=k).fit(X)\n",
    "    distances, _ = nbrs.kneighbors(X)\n",
    "    distances = np.sort(distances[:, -1])\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot the distances\n",
    "    plt.plot(distances)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Samples')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(f'{k}th Nearest Neighbor Distance')\n",
    "    plt.title(f'Knee Point for {k}th Nearest Neighbor')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_knee_point(normalized_data, k=5)"
   ]
  },
